OL,3,CThe impact of "news avoidance" on
OL,4,Cbroadcast news
OL,6,FIt might also be that they seek
OL,7,F"confirmation bias" ` articles which
OL,8,Freinforce their existing views.
OL,10,FThey might be reading individual
OL,11,Fpieces which are fair but which only
OL,12,Fone part of a complex story ` say an
OL,13,Farticle which looks solely at the
OL,14,Fplight of an individual family in
OL,15,FGaza.
OL,17,FMore disturbingly, there is simple
OL,18,Ffake news ` lies, deliberate
OL,19,Fmisinformation and conspiracies
OL,20,Fpresented as fact.
OL,26,@kD@OOUkD@^O]oD@AOUoD@SO]
